          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 7Be radioactive beam was produced and separated",
                " by the Momentum Achromatic Recoil Spectrometer",
                " (MARS)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "In both experiments, we determined target properties",
                " such as thickness and uniformity by using the",
                " radioactive 7Be and 8B beams directly by detecting",
                " beam particles at 0 degree with and without the",
                " target. The resultant energy loss measurements were",
                " compared with calculations made with the computer",
                " code SRIM to extract the thicknesses. In addition,",
                " offline measurements were made with a 228Th a source.",
                " The resulting target thicknesses were 1.54 +/- 0.06",
                " mg/cm2 formelamine and 1.9 +/- 0.1 mg/cm2 for C."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four 5 x 5 cm 900-microm-thick two-dimensional",
                " position sensitive silicon detector (PSSD)"
              ]
            }
          ],
